structure and function and its deficiency is linked to the
impairment in neuropsychologic functioning, activity, or
motor and cognitive development (Black 1998). Previous
review
represented
the
role
of
zinc
and
beneficial
responses to zinc supplements in some disorders of the
central nervous system such as Parkinson’s disease, schizo-
phrenia, depression and Alzheimer’s disease (Portbury and
Adlard 2017). Hence, zinc supplement might be very use-
ful to be added in the dietary guidelines in patients
with ADHD.
